After immobilization of probe and hybridization of target and capture strands on the gold surface, MB-CDs were added to bind to the mismatched sites. Different MB-CDs were incubated with immobilized double helix DNA and then the fluorescence intensities of suspensions were monitored. The incubation time of 1 h for the incubation MB-CDs with the formed ds-DNA on the gold surface was obtained (Fig. 3
                        ). It is expected that each mismatch only hybridizes with the complementary MB-CDs and the fluorescence intensities of the other MB-CDs will not change significantly. Therefore, the exposure A-C mismatch site (H1-target) with 4 different MB-CDs, gust decrease the fluorescence intensities of G-CDs and T-CDs but no significant changes in fluorescence intensities of C-CDs and A-CDs were observed. On the other side, H2 target (G-T mismatch) just affects the fluorescence intensities of A-CDs and C-CDs and no effect on G-CDs and T-CDs (Fig. 4
                        ).

The dependency of the ΔF to different concentrations of each mismatch target was also investigated and linear relations between ΔF and the logarithm of target concentrations for different MB-CDs in nanomolar ranges and limit of detections in picomolar ranges were obtained (Fig. 5
                        ). Based on these results, the presented assay can discriminate (genotype) various mismatches and also can determine the concentration of each target strand in an appropriate linear range with acceptable detection limits as listed in Table 1
                        . The differences between the linear ranges and detection limits can be attributed to the difference between the destabilizing of the duplex structure of DNA in the presence of H1 (A-C) and H2 (G-T) targets. The incorporation of G-T mismatch slightly destabilizes a duplex structure of ds-DNA, while C-A mismatch significantly destabilizes it [36]. Therefore, the accessibility to the nucleotide in the A-C mismatch sites is much higher than G-T mismatch sites and lower limit of detections was observed for H1 targets.
